ğŸ‡¬ğŸ‡§THE EARTH DOES NOT SPIN Granting heliocentrists their atmospheric glue assumption helps them dismiss the results of experiments on vertically fired cannonballs, but does not and cannot help them explain the results of cardinally fired horizontal cannonballs. Similarly, granting them their magic velcro helps rule out the results of experiments on hovering helicopters and hot air balloons, but does not and cannot explain the results of airplanes flying in cardinal directions. For example, if the Earth and its lower atmosphere are supposedly spinning together eastward at 1,000 miles per hour at the equator, then airplane pilots would need to do an extra 1,000 mph offset acceleration when flying westward! Pilots bound north and south would, of necessity, have to set diagonal bearings to compensate! Since such compensations are never necessary, except in the imagination of astronomers, it follows that the Earth does not move.
